Rating: 4
After reading all the excellent reviews, I decided to try this for our Passover Sedar. It was a big hit with everyone! I cut down the white sugar to 1 cup and the brown sugar to 1/3 cup. Make sure to have 4 cups of tart apples,(even if you use more than 4). When preparing,I added the apple mixture, raisins and apricots to the soaked matzoh and tossed together; then beat the eggs, white sugar, salt, cinammon and melted butter together; then folded the egg mixture into the fruit/matzoh mixture. The results were delicious!!!

